{"ts": "2026-06-09T00:06:16.740514+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: 761394d4c1bc093dffd57dd9d470512c6d645aaf)", "id": "lc_54ad0608-8889-4783-b0d0-cdb250fb3206"}, {"type": "text", "text": "# Default profile set shipped with vidpack.\n# Edit to customize or add profiles. Profile names must be lowercase ASCII.\n\n[web]\ncontainer = \"mp4\"\nvideo_codec = \"libx264\"\naudio_codec = \"aac\"\nvideo_bitrate = \"2M\"\nscale = \"1280:720\"\n\n[archive]\ncontainer = \"mkv\"\nvideo_codec = \"libx265\"\naudio_codec = \"flac\"\ncrf = 18\nscale = \"source\"\n\n[gif]\ncontainer = \"gif\"\nfps = 12\nscale = \"480:-1\"\n# Note: the gif profile currently uses a single-pass palette generation,\n# which is convenient but produces noticeably worse quality than a proper\n# two-pass palettegen / paletteuse pipeline. Known limitation; tracked in\n# the issue tracker.\n", "id": "lc_30f4d4f0-1e81-46ac-9fa0-68cc5d257c6d"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "9a959fff-18b1-4b3c-bc32-e7cca97bdad6", "tool_call_id": "call_87934addd3cb43889f2b3cc3", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-09T00:06:34.071305+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "When you run `vidpack`, you can select one of the three encoding profiles defined in `profiles.toml`. Each profile produces a specific container format and uses the following codecs:\n\n| Profile | Container | Video Codec | Audio Codec |\n|---------|-----------|-------------|-------------|\n| `web` | `.mp4` | `libx264` (H.264) | `aac` |\n| `archive` | `.mkv` | `libx265` (H.265/HEVC) | `flac` |\n| `gif` | `.gif` | Palette‑based (no standard codec) | None |\n\n**Details:**\n- **`web`** – Targets 720p at a 2 Mbps video bitrate, packaged in an MP4 container.\n- **`archive`** – Keeps the source resolution, encodes at CRF 18 (near‑lossless), and stores the result in an MKV container with lossless audio (FLAC).\n- **`gif`** – Scales to 480 p wide at 12 fps; the output is an animated GIF (no audio). The README notes that the current single‑pass palette generation is a known quality limitation.\n\nThese are the defaults shipped with the repository; you can edit `profiles.toml` to add or modify profiles.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 520, "prompt_tokens": 3406, "total_tokens": 3926, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 225, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 3072, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.0006087492, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 0.0001563492, "upstream_inference_completions_cost": 0.0004524}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-20260422", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "gen-1780963577-rVmsxovaGq4S4owaMlKi", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea9b3-8ba5-7e62-8615-69